quran[5]{c,v,t}:
  16,66,"Verily, you have in cattle a lesson; We give you to drink from that which is in their belly, betwixt excretions and blood, pure milk, agreeable for drinkers"
  16,67,"And of the fruit of the palms and the grapes you derive drinks and goodly nourishment; verily, in that is a sign to a people who have sense"
  16,68,"And your Lord inspired the bee, \"Take to habitations in the mountains and in the trees, and in the habitations of men"
  16,69,"Then eat from every fruit, and walk in the beaten paths of your Lord\". There comes forth from her body a draught varying in hue, in which is a healing for mankind. Verily, herein are, indeed, signs unto a people who reflect"
  16,70,"Allah created you; then He will take you to Himself; but amongst you are some whom He will thrust into the most decrepit stage of life, so that he may not know aught that once he knew. Verily, Allah is Knower, Powerful"